    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="1564"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1564">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.404/16.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Canada</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1041.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate, <lb/> Veracruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 25, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit inclosed herewith an
                    order from the Governor of the State of Veracruz to the Military Authorities
                    relative to the clergy.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. W. Canada</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head"
                        >[Untitled]</head>
                    <p rend="center">[From Official Gazette of September 19, 1914.]</p>
                    <p rend="center">
                        <hi rend="italic">Decree concerning clergy</hi>.</p>
                    <p>Office of the Secretary of the Constitutionalist Government of the Free and
                        Sovereign State of Veracruz.</p>
                    <p>In order to explain the resolution made by the Governor and Military
                        Commander of the State, General Candido Aguilar, relative to the clergy, I
                        hereby make known that he has ordered the definite expulsion of the foreign
                        clergymen, permitting the nationals to exercise their functions, in the
                        following proportions.</p>
                    <p>In towns: of 500 to 10,000 inhabitants, one priest; of 10,000 to 30,000
                        inhabitants, two priests; from 30,000 upwards, up to four priests as a
                        maximum.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <dateline rendition="#left">
                            <placeName>Jalapa</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1914-09-11">11th of September, 1914.</date> Government
                            Secretary, Heriberto Jara.</dateline>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
